# HSE Extraction Prompt — Full 10-Section Schema

> This is the exact prompt used in the Day 2 comparison study. Both ChatGPT and Claude received this identical prompt along with the ExxonMobil 2025 Sustainability Report PDF.

---

## Prompt

```
You are a senior HSE data analyst. Extract ALL key information from this 
HSE report with zero omissions. Structure your output exactly as specified 
below. Write NULL for any missing field. Flag ambiguous values.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 1 — REPORT METADATA
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Extract:
- Report Title
- Reporting Organization / Company Name
- Report Period (Start Date, End Date)
- Publication / Issue Date
- Report Version or ID
- Applicable Standards (ISO 14001, ISO 45001, GRI, IOGP, etc.)
- Third-Party Assurance Provider (if any)
- Assurance Level (Reasonable / Limited / None)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 2 — SAFETY PERFORMANCE KPIs
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Extract ALL numeric safety metrics. For each:

| KPI Name | Value | Unit | Year | Benchmark | Trend vs Prior Year |
|----------|-------|------|------|-----------|---------------------|

Required KPIs to look for (write NULL if absent):
- Total Recordable Incident Rate (TRIR)
- Lost Time Incident Rate (LTIR)
- Fatal Accident Rate (FAR)
- Number of Fatalities (employees / contractors separately)
- Near-Miss Count
- First Aid Cases
- Process Safety Tier 1 Events
- Process Safety Tier 2 Events
- Days Away From Work Rate (DAFWR)
- Severity Rate
- Work Hours (total, employees, contractors)
- Contractor vs Employee split for all rates

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 3 — HEALTH PERFORMANCE KPIs
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Extract ALL numeric health metrics:

| KPI Name | Value | Unit | Year | Notes |
|----------|-------|------|------|-------|

Required KPIs to look for:
- Occupational Illness Rate
- Occupational Illness Cases (count)
- Health Surveillance Coverage (%)
- Workforce Health Program Participation (%)
- Medical Removal Cases
- Mental Health Program Metrics (if any)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 4 — ENVIRONMENTAL PERFORMANCE KPIs
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Extract ALL numeric environmental metrics:

| KPI Name | Value | Raw Value | Converted Value | Unit | Year | Scope | Source Page |
|----------|-------|-----------|-----------------|------|------|-------|-------------|

Conversion rules — apply automatically:
- $XM → multiply by 1,000,000
- $XB → multiply by 1,000,000,000
- X% → keep as numeric (e.g., 25% → 25)
- ">X" or "~X" → extract numeric, flag ambiguity = YES
- Pounds → note as non-SI

Required KPIs to look for:
- GHG Emissions Scope 1 (absolute + intensity)
- GHG Emissions Scope 2 (market-based + location-based)
- GHG Emissions Scope 3 (by category if available)
- Methane Emissions (absolute + intensity)
- Flaring Volume
- NOx Emissions
- SOx Emissions
- VOC Emissions
- Freshwater Withdrawal (by source)
- Freshwater Consumption
- Water Intensity (by business unit)
- Wastewater Discharged
- Total Waste Generated (hazardous / non-hazardous)
- Waste Recycled / Diverted from Landfill (%)
- Waste to Landfill
- Hydrocarbon Spills (count + volume)
- Non-Hydrocarbon Spills (count + volume)
- Energy Consumption (total + by fuel type)
- Energy Intensity
- Biodiversity Impact Area (hectares)
- Land Remediated
- Environmental Fines and Penalties

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 5 — INCIDENTS & EVENTS LOG
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
For EVERY incident, event, or case mentioned extract:

| Incident ID | Date | Location | Facility Type | Incident Type | 
| Severity Level | Root Cause | Corrective Action | Status | Source Page |

Severity classification — standardize to:
CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW / NEAR-MISS

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 6 — REGULATORY & COMPLIANCE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Extract:
- List of applicable regulations mentioned
- Compliance status for each (COMPLIANT / NON-COMPLIANT / PARTIAL / NULL)
- Number of regulatory violations (count)
- Fines issued (amount + currency + year)
- Ongoing investigations (count + description)
- Permits held (count)
- Permit violations (count)
- Audit findings (count by severity)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 7 — TARGETS & COMMITMENTS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
For every target or goal mentioned extract:

| Target Description | Baseline Year | Baseline Value | 
| Target Year | Target Value | Current Value | 
| % Progress | On Track (Yes/No/NULL) | Source Page |

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 8 — PROGRAMS & INITIATIVES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
For every HSE program or initiative mentioned extract:

| Program Name | Type (Safety/Health/Environment/Combined) |
| Geographic Scope | Investment Amount | People Reached |
| Start Year | KPI/Outcome Reported | Source Page |

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 9 — WORKFORCE & CONTRACTOR DATA
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
Extract:
- Total Workforce (headcount)
- Employee Count
- Contractor Count
- Total Work Hours (employees + contractors)
- Training Hours (total + per employee)
- HSE Training Completion Rate (%)
- Number of HSE Drills Conducted
- Emergency Response Exercises (count)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 10 — DATA QUALITY FLAGS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
After extraction, produce a quality audit table:

| Row/KPI Reference | Flag Type | Description | Recommended Action |

Flag types to apply:
- APPROXIMATION → value uses ~, >, <, "approximately", "about"
- MULTI-YEAR → value spans multiple years without annual breakdown
- NON-SI UNIT → value in non-metric unit (pounds, gallons, etc.)
- RESTATED → value differs from prior year report for same period
- SCOPE UNCLEAR → it is unclear if value covers operated assets only,
                   equity share, or full value chain
- DUPLICATE → same metric appears in multiple sections
- MISSING DENOMINATOR → rate/intensity given without base quantity
- UNVERIFIED → no third-party assurance for this data point

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
OUTPUT RULES — MANDATORY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════
1. Do NOT summarize. Extract every numeric KPI — zero omissions.
2. Do NOT interpret or infer values not explicitly stated.
3. Write NULL for every missing field — never leave blank.
4. Keep raw values AND converted values in separate columns.
5. Record source page number for every single row.
6. If a metric appears in multiple sections of the report,
   extract all instances as separate rows and note DUPLICATE flag.
7. Standardize all years to YYYY format.
8. Standardize all currencies to USD where conversion is possible;
   note original currency if not USD.
9. For every rate metric confirm and record the denominator
   (e.g., per 200,000 work hours vs per 1,000,000 work hours).
10. Output sections sequentially — do not skip any section
    even if all values are NULL.
```

---

## Notes on Prompt Design

### What worked well
- The mandatory NULL rule made omissions visible and auditable
- Explicit KPI checklists per section ensured both models had the same target list
- Denominator specification (per 200K vs per 1M work hours) caught a common HSE benchmarking confusion
- Dual raw/converted columns made unit approximations explicit

### What could be improved
- Adding "prioritise structured data tables and appendices over narrative text" may help models that exhibit positional bias toward document introductions
- Specifying "page 67-69 contains the primary performance data table" as an explicit hint could guide models to the right source
- Adding "do not use narrative trend statements as substitutes for actual measured values" could prevent the 25% / emission value confusion seen in ChatGPT's output

